1
00:00:00,667 --> 00:00:01,800
<i> He's the son of the enemy.</i>

2
00:00:01,800 --> 00:00:02,767
<i> Of course, he'd side
with his dad.</i>

3
00:00:02,767 --> 00:00:04,167
<i> Don't you get what I'm saying?</i>

4
00:00:04,167 --> 00:00:05,733
<i> He hasn't done anything wrong.</i>

5
00:00:05,733 --> 00:00:07,733
<i> How are you so sure?</i>

6
00:00:07,733 --> 00:00:09,733
<i>Do you monitor his every move
all day, all week?</i>

7
00:00:09,733 --> 00:00:12,333
<i>Like you, I just want
to know the truth.</i>

8
00:00:12,333 --> 00:00:13,400
<i> Aah!</i>

9
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:14,733
<i> Why did you follow us?</i>

10
00:00:14,733 --> 00:00:17,333
<i>You might get lost.
I've been there before.</i>

11
00:00:17,333 --> 00:00:18,567
<i> Looks like they found it.</i>

12
00:00:18,567 --> 00:00:20,000
- [GUNSHOT]
- [GASPS]

13
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,567
<i> Hurry! Run!</i>

14
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:25,000
<i> Just take me!</i>

15
00:00:25,633 --> 00:00:28,467
<i> This is where it leads.
To this church.</i>

16
00:00:28,467 --> 00:00:30,433
<i> We should find something here.</i>

17
00:00:34,533 --> 00:00:41,467
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

18
00:00:42,467 --> 00:00:44,167
[WOODEN CHAIR THUDS]

19
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:50,000
[WOODEN CHAIR THUDS]

20
00:00:56,433 --> 00:00:57,767
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

21
00:01:02,733 --> 00:01:04,433
[BIRDS CONTINUE CHIRPING]

22
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:15,667
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

23
00:01:22,433 --> 00:01:25,233
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

24
00:01:37,700 --> 00:01:42,100
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

25
00:01:42,133 --> 00:01:44,200
[RUSTLING]

26
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:50,767
[JADE] Kiko? Edward?

27
00:01:51,867 --> 00:01:53,233
Kiko! Edward!

28
00:01:54,267 --> 00:01:55,167
Jade?

29
00:01:55,667 --> 00:01:56,633
Jade?

30
00:01:59,633 --> 00:02:00,600
Jade.

31
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,233
- Jade.
- Jade.

32
00:02:02,233 --> 00:02:03,767
- Are you okay?
- Are you okay?

33
00:02:05,833 --> 00:02:09,300
Kiko, can you please check
the last part?

34
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:16,367
"Read the line like a vow...

35
00:02:17,567 --> 00:02:20,100
Because that's where
it breathes...

36
00:02:21,167 --> 00:02:22,733
The oscalera"

37
00:02:25,767 --> 00:02:28,133
Jade, you found it.

38
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:33,867
We're on the right track.

39
00:02:33,867 --> 00:02:40,367
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

40
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:48,733
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

41
00:03:39,967 --> 00:03:45,167
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

42
00:03:45,367 --> 00:03:47,500
Is this the Oscalera?

43
00:03:47,667 --> 00:03:49,667
Is that what this church
is called?

44
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:53,000
I feel like we're
missing something.

45
00:03:56,233 --> 00:03:59,767
"Read the line like a vow...

46
00:03:59,767 --> 00:04:02,800
Because that's where
it breathes... The Oscalera"

47
00:04:05,300 --> 00:04:08,767
You know what?
Let's keep looking.

48
00:04:10,433 --> 00:04:12,100
What else are we looking for?

49
00:04:12,100 --> 00:04:14,433
Do we have to start digging
or something?

50
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:17,367
W-Where is he going?

51
00:04:18,167 --> 00:04:19,967
Let's just look around again.

52
00:04:19,967 --> 00:04:21,833
- We might be able to--
- Hey!

53
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:23,733
- What are you doing, huh?!
- Kiko! Kiko!

54
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,333
- Calling to report to someone?!
- What the heck?!

55
00:04:25,433 --> 00:04:28,067
- What are you saying?!
- You really can't be trusted!

56
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:28,767
Kiko!

57
00:04:29,033 --> 00:04:31,933
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

58
00:04:34,133 --> 00:04:41,133
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

59
00:04:45,767 --> 00:04:47,867
Wait, wait, wait.

60
00:04:47,867 --> 00:04:49,333
- Wait!
- Sari, are you alright?

61
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:51,267
- Wait a second.
- What's wrong?

62
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:54,067
Wait...

63
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:57,100
I think we've already
passed by this tree.

64
00:04:59,033 --> 00:05:00,200
You're right.

65
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:03,033
I remember that tree.
But we've been walking straight.

66
00:05:05,933 --> 00:05:06,667
Oh no.

67
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:08,167
Sari...

68
00:05:08,900 --> 00:05:10,400
What are you...

69
00:05:13,633 --> 00:05:15,633
Why are you stripping?!

70
00:05:15,633 --> 00:05:18,000
[SARI] I'm not stripping, sir!

71
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:19,967
I'm just wearing my clothes
inside out because--

72
00:05:19,967 --> 00:05:21,600
Because we're lost?

73
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:26,700
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

74
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:30,000
Jade, look at how he's acting!
Do you really trust this guy?

75
00:05:31,367 --> 00:05:34,867
You're calling your father to
report what we saw, aren't you?

76
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:37,233
Jade, I saw him!
He was making a call!

77
00:05:37,233 --> 00:05:38,733
I wasn't calling Dad!

78
00:05:39,700 --> 00:05:41,667
I was calling to rent
some ATV

79
00:05:41,667 --> 00:05:43,067
so we can have a ride home!

80
00:05:43,067 --> 00:05:44,600
Stop with the excuses!

81
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:47,167
Fine. Jade, check my phone.

82
00:05:47,933 --> 00:05:49,133
Look!

83
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:54,333
You won't see any log
of me calling my Dad.

84
00:05:57,500 --> 00:06:01,033
Kiko, I checked.
He wasn't calling his dad.

85
00:06:02,633 --> 00:06:04,133
Kiko, can you calm down?

86
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:08,267
Pleases stop thinking ill
of Edward right now.

87
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:11,567
Just this once.
Just while we're searching.

88
00:06:12,733 --> 00:06:14,767
Jade, you can't blame me
for suspecting him.

89
00:06:15,867 --> 00:06:19,100
I'll keep an eye on him
while he's with us.

90
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:25,967
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

91
00:06:28,233 --> 00:06:29,900
If it weren't for you...

92
00:06:30,967 --> 00:06:32,700
I'd have already
beaten him up.

93
00:06:32,700 --> 00:06:39,600
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

94
00:06:44,933 --> 00:06:45,900
[KIKO EXHALES SHARPLY]

95
00:06:46,933 --> 00:06:49,033
Sir, I'm really sorry.

96
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:52,067
It's fine. Just put on
your clothes properly.

97
00:06:52,067 --> 00:06:53,933
But, sir, we're lost!

98
00:06:53,933 --> 00:06:55,767
Get dressed first.

99
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:58,700
Tsk!

100
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:02,933
You done?

101
00:07:02,933 --> 00:07:04,033
[SARI] Wait!

102
00:07:10,167 --> 00:07:11,533
Okay, I'm done.

103
00:07:14,667 --> 00:07:16,233
You have quite the girlfriend.

104
00:07:16,233 --> 00:07:17,233
Girlfriend?

105
00:07:18,133 --> 00:07:20,200
S-Sari is not my girlfriend.

106
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:27,067
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

107
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:31,200
Okay.

108
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:36,000
It's getting dark soon.

109
00:07:36,833 --> 00:07:38,000
We should go back.

110
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:41,800
How are we going to get back?
We're lost.

111
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:43,233
[JUSTIN]
And we've come this far.

112
00:07:43,233 --> 00:07:45,067
It'd be a waste
if we go back now.

113
00:07:45,900 --> 00:07:49,100
Maybe we'll find the right way
tomorrow when the sun's back up.

114
00:07:50,733 --> 00:07:52,633
Sir Justin is right.

115
00:07:52,633 --> 00:07:55,100
Let's look for a place
to stay the night.

116
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:59,267
Fine.

117
00:08:02,067 --> 00:08:03,133
Okay.

118
00:08:10,033 --> 00:08:13,033
I'll lead the way if you
don't know where you're going.

119
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:24,867
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

120
00:08:44,733 --> 00:08:51,633
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

121
00:08:53,667 --> 00:08:55,933
Well? Did you find anything?

122
00:08:58,033 --> 00:08:59,833
We've searched the entire area.

123
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,833
But still nothing.

124
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:03,933
And it's getting dark.

125
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:07,700
We should head home
before the sun goes down

126
00:09:07,700 --> 00:09:09,000
and just go back tomorrow.

127
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:12,200
Excited to go home?

128
00:09:13,100 --> 00:09:14,300
Why?

129
00:09:14,300 --> 00:09:17,000
Can't wait to report to
your father about what we found?

130
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,267
- Kiko, stop it.
- And tomorrow...

131
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:21,233
...you'll come here
before us.

132
00:09:21,233 --> 00:09:22,867
[SCOFFS]

133
00:09:24,733 --> 00:09:26,233
Kiko, you're starting
to get on my nerves.

134
00:09:26,233 --> 00:09:29,200
- Stop it! Let's just go!
- You keep accusing me!

135
00:09:29,233 --> 00:09:33,000
What, are you expecting me
to just trust you?

136
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,000
Have you done anything
to earn it?

137
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,100
Kiko!

138
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:43,867
You're exhausting.

139
00:09:43,867 --> 00:09:50,800
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

140
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:55,567
Edward.

141
00:09:58,300 --> 00:09:59,533
Edward!

142
00:10:09,467 --> 00:10:10,867
[LUNA GROANS]

143
00:10:14,767 --> 00:10:15,900
[GASPS]

144
00:10:17,267 --> 00:10:22,300
[PANIC BREATHING]

145
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:29,233
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

146
00:10:29,233 --> 00:10:30,367
Gio...

147
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:32,967
Gio.

148
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:35,067
Gio, please.

149
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:36,467
Please wake up, Gio!

150
00:10:37,267 --> 00:10:38,200
Gio!

151
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:46,033
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

152
00:10:46,167 --> 00:10:47,500
[LUNA BREATHES HEAVILY]

153
00:10:47,633 --> 00:10:48,767
[WHISPERS] Gio.

154
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:50,733
Gio!

155
00:10:53,733 --> 00:10:55,100
[LUNA] Gio, please wake up.

156
00:10:55,833 --> 00:10:56,767
Gio!

157
00:10:57,300 --> 00:10:58,200
Gio!

158
00:11:09,167 --> 00:11:10,167
Luna?

159
00:11:10,300 --> 00:11:11,267
Are you okay?

160
00:11:14,033 --> 00:11:14,700
Luna!

161
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:21,900
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

162
00:11:25,033 --> 00:11:26,100
[JUSTIN SIGHS]

163
00:11:33,867 --> 00:11:36,133
I think we can stay here
for the night.

164
00:11:37,633 --> 00:11:38,600
[MUSIC FADES]

165
00:11:38,733 --> 00:11:40,500
If we hadn't been lost,

166
00:11:40,633 --> 00:11:43,700
we might have reached
the shrine.

167
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,367
I'm sorry, Sir Martin.

168
00:11:47,300 --> 00:11:48,167
Sir Justin.

169
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:49,767
It's alright, Sari.

170
00:11:49,900 --> 00:11:51,400
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

171
00:11:51,533 --> 00:11:55,100
It's okay if you scold me, sir.

172
00:11:55,233 --> 00:11:57,133
I told you it's alright.

173
00:11:58,333 --> 00:12:00,200
Come on, have a rest.

174
00:12:02,267 --> 00:12:03,300
Stay here.

175
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:14,733
This should be fine.

176
00:12:19,233 --> 00:12:20,167
[GRUNTS]

177
00:12:23,667 --> 00:12:25,067
[MARTIN GRUNTS SOFTLY]

178
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:37,333
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

179
00:12:41,733 --> 00:12:44,433
[MUSIC TURNS FOREBODING]

180
00:12:44,567 --> 00:12:46,600
[GIO] Where-- Where are we?

181
00:12:46,733 --> 00:12:48,333
[LUNA] I don't know!

182
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:49,767
[PABLO] At my house.

183
00:12:54,133 --> 00:12:55,200
Let us go!

184
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:58,667
Please let us go!
We don't mean anything bad!

185
00:13:01,067 --> 00:13:02,167
What were you doing
in my house?

186
00:13:02,300 --> 00:13:03,867
Don't you know
what trespassing is?

187
00:13:05,033 --> 00:13:07,133
I'm sorry, we didn't know
someone was living here.

188
00:13:09,300 --> 00:13:10,433
Who else came with you?

189
00:13:13,767 --> 00:13:15,800
No one. It's just us two.

190
00:13:20,167 --> 00:13:23,000
[SHOVEL RATTLING]

191
00:13:23,967 --> 00:13:25,467
Then who are the people outside?

192
00:13:27,767 --> 00:13:29,400
- We don't know!
- [PABLO] Tell me the truth.

193
00:13:29,533 --> 00:13:30,500
I swear, we don't know!

194
00:13:30,633 --> 00:13:31,700
It's just the two of us
who came here!

195
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:33,367
There's no else with us!

196
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:35,433
If there's someone else outside,
they're not with us.

197
00:13:35,567 --> 00:13:36,700
We don't know them!

198
00:13:36,833 --> 00:13:37,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

199
00:13:37,867 --> 00:13:39,067
Let's see about that.

200
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:40,933
[GUN CLICKS]

201
00:13:42,067 --> 00:13:42,967
Luna!

202
00:13:43,367 --> 00:13:44,233
[MAN] Hurry up!

203
00:13:45,300 --> 00:13:46,300
Don't make any noise.

204
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:48,967
[SHOVEL RATTLING]

205
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,267
[GUNSHOT]

206
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:51,300
[BODY THUDS]

207
00:13:51,433 --> 00:13:52,367
[GUNSHOTS]

208
00:13:53,433 --> 00:13:58,667
[GUNSHOTS IN DISTANCE]

209
00:13:58,833 --> 00:14:00,400
[GIO GRUNTS]

210
00:14:04,333 --> 00:14:05,333
Hurry.

211
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,733
[GUNSHOTS]

212
00:14:08,867 --> 00:14:10,467
[GROANS] Agh!

213
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:11,567
[GUNSHOTS]

214
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:13,233
[GRUNTS] Argh, I got shot.

215
00:14:19,267 --> 00:14:26,100
[GIO PANTING]

216
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:33,367
- [GUNSHOT]
- [BODY THUDS, GROANS]

217
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:35,867
[GUNSHOTS CONTINUE]

218
00:14:36,933 --> 00:14:40,367
[GUNSHOTS IN DISTANCE]

219
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:41,900
Luna!

220
00:14:42,033 --> 00:14:43,767
[BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY]

221
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:46,367
[GUNSHOTS IN DISTANCE]

222
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:49,200
[BREATHING HEAVILY CONTINUES]

223
00:14:50,167 --> 00:14:51,067
Gio!

224
00:14:56,633 --> 00:14:58,367
- Argh!
- [GUN THUDS]

225
00:14:58,500 --> 00:14:59,900
[GUNSHOT]

226
00:15:00,033 --> 00:15:02,633
[BOTH GRUNTING]

227
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:03,933
[BLOW LANDS]

228
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,367
- [BLOWS LAND]
- [MAN GROANS]

229
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:11,133
- [BODIES THUD]
- [GRASS RUSTLING]

230
00:15:13,033 --> 00:15:16,033
[BOTH GRUNTING]

231
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:20,267
[PABLO CHOKING]

232
00:15:22,300 --> 00:15:23,400
[GUNSHOT]

233
00:15:23,533 --> 00:15:30,333
[PABLO COUGHING]

234
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:32,533
Are you okay?

235
00:15:33,900 --> 00:15:36,400
T-Thank you. [COUGHS]

236
00:15:36,567 --> 00:15:43,433
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

237
00:15:48,700 --> 00:15:50,900
I heard you talking
to Sari earlier.

238
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:55,567
Is it about Leon?

239
00:15:55,700 --> 00:15:56,733
[MARTIN] Mm-hmm.

240
00:15:58,867 --> 00:16:00,867
I guess I'm just good
at acting tough.

241
00:16:02,533 --> 00:16:06,133
But I feel like I can't do
anything to save my own brother

242
00:16:06,267 --> 00:16:08,000
from this situation right now.

243
00:16:08,967 --> 00:16:11,533
You are right here
with us right now.

244
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:15,033
You're also risking
your life here for Leon.

245
00:16:16,133 --> 00:16:17,433
Yes, I'm okay.

246
00:16:17,567 --> 00:16:23,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

247
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:25,867
We don't always see
each other eye to eye.

248
00:16:27,733 --> 00:16:29,033
But Justin...

249
00:16:31,167 --> 00:16:32,633
know that I'm here.

250
00:16:34,467 --> 00:16:36,467
Now that your brother
is in jail,

251
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,433
I can be your big brother
for now.

252
00:16:38,567 --> 00:16:45,633
[UPLIFTING MUSIC PLAYING]

253
00:16:49,433 --> 00:16:51,900
[MARTIN INHALES SHARPLY]

254
00:16:55,167 --> 00:16:56,400
[JUSTIN SCOFFS]

255
00:16:57,867 --> 00:16:59,567
Never let her go.

256
00:17:00,833 --> 00:17:03,000
A girl that's willing to put
herself in danger

257
00:17:03,133 --> 00:17:04,800
just to be with you?

258
00:17:04,933 --> 00:17:10,033
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

259
00:17:10,167 --> 00:17:12,200
What are you even talking about?

260
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:13,933
[JUSTIN] What am I
even talking about?

261
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:17,567
You should be thankful that
someone cares about you.

262
00:17:21,700 --> 00:17:24,667
[MARTIN] Just go to sleep.

263
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:27,633
Let's just take shifts.
I'll wake you up later.

264
00:17:27,767 --> 00:17:28,800
All right.

265
00:17:30,133 --> 00:17:32,400
[RUSTLING]

266
00:17:33,433 --> 00:17:34,933
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

267
00:17:35,067 --> 00:17:41,867
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

268
00:17:45,167 --> 00:17:46,633
[DOOR OPENS]

269
00:17:49,033 --> 00:17:49,900
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

270
00:17:50,033 --> 00:17:51,067
[DOOR SHUTS]

271
00:17:55,367 --> 00:17:57,567
[BOTTLES CLINKING]

272
00:17:58,767 --> 00:17:59,833
[EXHALES]

273
00:17:59,967 --> 00:18:00,967
[BACKPACK THUDS]

274
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,067
[EXHALES]

275
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:06,067
[GLASS CLINKS]

276
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:09,100
[WATER POURING]

277
00:18:09,233 --> 00:18:10,500
Hey, bud. Where were you?

278
00:18:10,633 --> 00:18:12,467
You seem really tired.

279
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:14,500
I was with Jade and Kiko.

280
00:18:15,233 --> 00:18:16,500
What did you do?

281
00:18:19,067 --> 00:18:20,100
I just accompanied them.

282
00:18:20,233 --> 00:18:21,267
We searched for some treasure.

283
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:25,233
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

284
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:26,667
Treasure?

285
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:29,700
You helped them look for
the treasure in Hotel 88?

286
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:35,033
[GLASS CLINKS]

287
00:18:35,167 --> 00:18:36,567
[ANDY] What did you find?

288
00:18:37,667 --> 00:18:39,500
So, did you manage to find it?

289
00:18:40,533 --> 00:18:42,133
Come on, bud, you can tell me.

290
00:18:42,267 --> 00:18:44,500
Where did you go?
Did you find it?

291
00:18:44,633 --> 00:18:51,667
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

292
00:18:56,967 --> 00:18:58,300
So, all this time,

293
00:18:58,433 --> 00:19:00,833
you already knew
about that treasure.

294
00:19:01,800 --> 00:19:03,267
[EDWARD]
So they were right

295
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:04,667
when they said
you were interested in it.

296
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:07,833
No, of course not.

297
00:19:07,967 --> 00:19:09,267
Tell me the truth!

298
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:11,633
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

299
00:19:11,767 --> 00:19:13,633
The reason why you want
to get Hotel 88

300
00:19:13,767 --> 00:19:16,133
is because you want
to get that treasure!

301
00:19:18,733 --> 00:19:23,033
We came to Hotel 88
for business.

302
00:19:23,167 --> 00:19:24,433
[ANDY] Business.

303
00:19:25,533 --> 00:19:27,733
I only heard rumors
about that treasure.

304
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:29,700
How could I know that's true?

305
00:19:29,833 --> 00:19:33,600
But now you tell me, you
actually went looking for it?

306
00:19:33,733 --> 00:19:35,467
If that's the case,
should we turn it down?

307
00:19:35,600 --> 00:19:36,733
It's for your future.

308
00:19:36,867 --> 00:19:40,000
I don't need anyone else's
money for my future!

309
00:19:42,333 --> 00:19:43,233
Okay.

310
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:46,133
Fine.

311
00:19:46,267 --> 00:19:49,067
I won't ask any more
questions about it, all right?

312
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:50,800
I was just curious.

313
00:19:50,933 --> 00:19:53,333
Did Leon get in jail
because of that treasure?

314
00:19:53,467 --> 00:19:57,200
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

315
00:19:57,333 --> 00:19:59,733
Were you the one who set him up?

316
00:20:01,667 --> 00:20:03,700
Is that how you really see me?

317
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,867
I don't know anymore, Dad.

318
00:20:12,167 --> 00:20:14,533
[EDWARD] With all the things
you've been hiding from me...

319
00:20:14,667 --> 00:20:17,967
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

320
00:20:18,100 --> 00:20:20,667
I don't know what should
I think of you.

321
00:20:29,433 --> 00:20:30,500
Edward.

322
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:33,500
Edward!

323
00:20:33,633 --> 00:20:40,667
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

324
00:20:45,267 --> 00:20:49,567
[AMBIENT NATURE SOUNDS]

325
00:20:49,700 --> 00:20:51,233
[INSECTS CHIRPING]

326
00:20:51,367 --> 00:20:58,167
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

327
00:21:00,967 --> 00:21:01,600
Sari?

328
00:21:03,300 --> 00:21:04,000
Sari?

329
00:21:06,233 --> 00:21:07,133
Sari?

330
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,167
Sari!

331
00:21:09,333 --> 00:21:10,233
Sari! Sa--

332
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:13,400
Justin. Wake up, Justin.
Sorry I fell asleep.

333
00:21:13,533 --> 00:21:14,367
Sari is missing.

334
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:16,567
- Why didn't you wake me up?
- I'm sorry!

335
00:21:16,700 --> 00:21:18,067
- Sari!
- Sari!

336
00:21:19,533 --> 00:21:20,400
- Sari!
- Sari!

337
00:21:21,767 --> 00:21:23,200
- Sari!
- Sari!

338
00:21:25,533 --> 00:21:27,633
- Sari!
- [JUSTIN] Sari!

339
00:21:27,767 --> 00:21:28,900
Sari!

340
00:21:30,533 --> 00:21:31,700
- Sari!
- [MARTIN] Sari!

341
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:33,967
[SARI WAILS IN DISTANCE]

342
00:21:34,100 --> 00:21:35,433
- Sari! Get my bag!
- Oh!

343
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,500
- Sari!
- [JUSTIN] Sari!

344
00:21:38,633 --> 00:21:45,433
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

345
00:21:58,967 --> 00:22:01,000
- [JADE] Leon.
- [FRIDA] Leon, son.

346
00:22:01,133 --> 00:22:01,833
Mom.

347
00:22:01,967 --> 00:22:03,467
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

348
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:12,000
[JADE, FRIDA SOBBING]

349
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:17,233
We'll come visit you there.

350
00:22:18,067 --> 00:22:19,433
[VOICE BREAKING] Take care.

351
00:22:22,300 --> 00:22:24,600
[FRIDA SOBS]

352
00:22:24,733 --> 00:22:27,533
Martin told me
to hug you for him.

353
00:22:33,533 --> 00:22:35,233
We are carrying out the plan.

354
00:22:35,367 --> 00:22:38,533
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

355
00:22:38,667 --> 00:22:40,067
[HENRI] Come on, let's go.

356
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:41,167
Take care.

357
00:22:42,133 --> 00:22:43,033
Leon...

358
00:22:44,833 --> 00:22:46,733
- Take care, Mom.
- [FRIDA SOBBING]

359
00:22:51,367 --> 00:22:52,800
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

360
00:22:56,633 --> 00:22:58,800
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

361
00:22:59,633 --> 00:23:00,767
[SNIFFLES]

362
00:23:12,867 --> 00:23:14,200
[CAR DOOR SHUTS]

363
00:23:14,333 --> 00:23:15,533
[CAR ENGINE REVS]

364
00:23:16,933 --> 00:23:18,033
[EXHALES FORCEFULLY]

365
00:23:18,167 --> 00:23:25,167
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

366
00:23:31,033 --> 00:23:32,200
<i>- Sari!
- Sari!</i>

367
00:23:32,333 --> 00:23:34,367
[SARI SQUEALS]

368
00:23:36,167 --> 00:23:38,367
<i>Why are you digging up
my grandma's grave?</i>

369
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:39,467
<i> We found a clue.</i>

370
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:40,500
<i> Clue?</i>

371
00:23:41,467 --> 00:23:42,967
<i>- Don't move!
- Put the gun down!</i>

372
00:23:43,100 --> 00:23:44,767
<i>Open the door
or else I'll kill him!</i>

373
00:23:44,900 --> 00:23:46,200
<i> Open the door!</i>

374
00:23:46,933 --> 00:23:48,067
<i> Sir, Leon got away.</i>

375
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:50,867
<i>If we don't find him,
our plans will be ruined.</i>

376
00:23:51,633 --> 00:23:52,600
<i> Surround the whole island.</i>

377
00:23:52,733 --> 00:23:53,933
<i> We can't let him get too far.</i>

378
00:23:56,167 --> 00:23:57,967
<i>You can't run away
from me, Almazan.</i>
